Controls to KEEP Enabled:

Audit rules - Keep all audit rules (R-258176 through R-258229) as they provide valuable logging
SSH hardening - Keep all SSH configurations
Password policies - Keep password complexity and aging rules
File permissions - Keep system file permission settings
Sysctl settings - Keep kernel hardening parameters
User account controls - Keep account management settings
Logging (rsyslog/auditd) - Keep system logging configurations

Additional Recommendations:

Network Time Protocol: Keep chrony enabled for time sync (important for logs)
Consider keeping:

Basic kernel module blacklisting (ATM, CAN, SCTP, TIPC) for attack surface reduction
Core security packages (sudo, audit, rsyslog)
User namespace restrictions (if not using containers)


Azure-Specific Considerations:

Ensure Azure Linux Agent is not blocked by any settings
Verify network settings don't interfere with Azure networking
Consider Azure Security Center recommendations alongside STIG
